## Gate Rule (MUST READ BEFORE ANY WORK)

This repository is labeled "{{ repo_label }}".

Analyze the Jira issue thoroughly — read the title, description, scope, and
acceptance criteria. Proceed only if you genuinely believe changes are
required in **this** repository ({{ repository }}).

Check the Jira issue description for phrases like:
- "No {{ repo_label }} changes required"
- "{{ repo_label }} N/A"
- "Out of Scope: {{ repo_label }} changes"
- "{{ repo_label }} changes" listed under "Out of Scope"
- "{{ repo_label }} changes: N/A"

If the issue explicitly excludes {{ repo_label }} work:
   → STOP. Do NOT make any changes.
   → Post a comment: "No changes needed in {{ repository }} ({{ repo_label }})."
   → Your job is done for this repository.

If the issue requires {{ repo_label }} changes:
   → Proceed with implementation below.

